item.description:
Optimisation problems generally take the following form;
 objective function(s) decision variables constraints.  The goal is to find values for the decision variables that optimise (maximise or minimise) the objective function within a set of given constraints. A linear programming problem (“LP”) is an optimisation problem for which:
 We seek to maximise (or minimise) a linear function of the decision variables. For any variable x we must have either x is nonnegative or is unrestricted in sign.
